mes.com/science/can-people-be-allergic-to-water-scientists-say-this-rare-condition-makes-it-possible/articleshow/131219385.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/can-people-be-allergic-to-water-scientists-say-this-rare-condition-makes-it-possible/articleshow/131219385.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T12:24:07+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131219392,imgsize-1083657.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Watch: PM Modi's surprise gift for Giorgia Meloni has a very 'Melodi' twist]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131219011.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni shared a video thanking Prime Minister Narendra Modi for gifting her 'Melody' chocolates. The term, a blend of their surnames, gained popularity during their previous meetings. This latest viral moment occurred during Modi's visit to Rome, focused on strengthening India-Italy ties across various sectors.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/watch-pm-modis-surprise-gift-for-giorgia-meloni-has-a-very-melodi-twist/articleshow/131219011.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/watch-pm-modis-surprise-gift-for-giorgia-meloni-has-a-very-melodi-twist/articleshow/131219011.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T12:12:23+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131219067,imgsize-40376.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Did regime change plans in Iran include hardliner who called to 'wipe Israel off the map'?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131215500.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[US and Israel reportedly explored a regime-change plan in Iran, centering on former President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad, after alleged strikes killed top officials and the Supreme Leader.  The plan, devised by Mossad, aimed to install Ahmadinejad, despite his hardline past, but collapsed after an Israeli strike on his residence. His current whereabouts are unknown.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/did-regime-change-plans-in-iran-include-hardliner-who-called-to-wipe-israel-off-the-map/articleshow/131215500.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/did-regime-change-plans-in-iran-include-hardliner-who-called-to-wipe-israel-off-the-map/articleshow/131215500.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T08:52:14+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131218038,imgsize-37178.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quote of the day by Marcus Aurelius: “It is not death that a man should fear, but he should fear…”]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131216721.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-marcus-aurelius-it-is-not-death-that-a-man-should-fear-but-he-should-fear/articleshow/131216721.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-marcus-aurelius-it-is-not-death-that-a-man-should-fear-but-he-should-fear/articleshow/131216721.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T10:48:28+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131217246,imgsize-35536.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[11 ancient archaeological discoveries that may completely rewrite everything we know about human history]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131216086.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/11-ancient-archaeological-discoveries-that-may-completely-rewrite-everything-we-know-about-human-history/articleshow/131216086.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/11-ancient-archaeological-discoveries-that-may-completely-rewrite-everything-we-know-about-human-history/articleshow/131216086.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T10:09:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131216437,imgsize-95392.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistan's claim of hitting 2 Indian airbases falls apart over one detail: The locations don't exist]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131215769.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Pakistan has made a bizarre claim of hitting two non-existent airbases, Rajouri and Mamun, during their counter-action "Operation Bunyan Ul Marsoos." This follows India's strong retaliatory action last year, where all Pakistani missiles and drone swarms were intercepted and destroyed by India's air defence.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistans-claim-of-hitting-2-indian-airbases-falls-apart-over-one-detail-the-locations-dont-exist/articleshow/131215769.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistans-claim-of-hitting-2-indian-airbases-falls-apart-over-one-detail-the-locations-dont-exist/articleshow/131215769.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T09:26:55+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131215959,imgsize-949176.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Melodi' moment in Rome: Italy PM Meloni welcomes 'friend' PM Modi with selfie and a warm message]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131215193.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni welcomed Narendra Modi to Rome for discussions aimed at elevating bilateral ties to a special strategic partnership. The visit focuses on strengthening cooperation, particularly through the India-Middle East-Europe Economic Corridor (IMEC), and includes plans for annual summits and a trade target of 20 billion euros by 2029.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/melodi-moment-in-rome-italy-pm-meloni-welcomes-friend-pm-modi-with-selfie-and-a-warm-message/articleshow/131215193.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/melodi-moment-in-rome-italy-pm-meloni-welcomes-friend-pm-modi-with-selfie-and-a-warm-message/articleshow/131215193.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T08:45:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131215411,imgsize-867387.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Locked and loaded': JD Vance warns US could restart military campaign if Iran talks fail]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131214254.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[US Vice President JD Vance stated that President Trump is pursuing a diplomatic deal with Iran but is prepared to resume military action if nuclear talks fail. Vance emphasized that the administration is negotiating in good faith, making it clear Iran will not be allowed to obtain a nuclear weapon.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/locked-and-loaded-jd-vance-warns-us-could-restart-military-campaign-if-iran-talks-fail/articleshow/131214254.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/locked-and-loaded-jd-vance-warns-us-could-restart-military-campaign-if-iran-talks-fail/articleshow/131214254.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T07:32:34+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131214319,imgsize-974040.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why was Jack Doherty placed under house arrest? Controversial streamer sparks backlash with ankle monitor video]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131213461.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Jack Doherty claimed he was placed under house arrest after posting a video showing an ankle monitor and saying he must stay home for the next few months. The update sparked major backlash online, with critics mocking the controversial streamer over his past behavior and legal troubles. Doherty was previously arrested in Florida on drug-related charges and later faced a PGA Tour ban after allegedly trespassing and disrupting an event.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/why-was-jack-doherty-placed-under-house-arrest-controversial-streamer-sparks-backlash-with-ankle-monitor-video/articleshow/131213461.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/why-was-jack-doherty-placed-under-house-arrest-controversial-streamer-sparks-backlash-with-ankle-monitor-video/articleshow/131213461.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T05:23:18+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131213461,imgsize-61872.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[What happened between Adin Ross and Anthony Fantano after Drake mentioned the streamer in Iceman lyrics?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131213294.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Anthony Fantano criticized Drake’s Adin Ross lyric during his Iceman livestream review, leading Adin Ross to respond with harsh comments and personal attacks. The argument quickly spread online because of Fantano’s long history of negative Drake reviews and Ross’ close relationship with the rapper through streaming collaborations and public appearances.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/what-happened-between-adin-ross-and-anthony-fantano-after-drake-mentioned-the-streamer-in-iceman-lyrics/articleshow/131213294.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/what-happened-between-adin-ross-and-anthony-fantano-after-drake-mentioned-the-streamer-in-iceman-lyrics/articleshow/131213294.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T04:26:40+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sehjal Gupta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131213291,imgsize-718748.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[QTCinderella lands CAA representation amid growing mainstream success]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131211072.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Twitch streamer and YouTube personality QTCinderella, whose real name is Blaire, has signed with the prominent Creative Artists Agency. This significant deal is expected to propel her career further, opening doors to television appearances, movies, and larger brand collaborations beyond her established online success with events like the Streamer Awards.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/qtcinderella-lands-caa-representation-amid-growing-mainstream-success/articleshow/131211072.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/qtcinderella-lands-caa-representation-amid-growing-mainstream-success/articleshow/131211072.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T02:45:10+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131211075,imgsize-595070.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian man says US is no longer a default upgrade: 3 types of people should not come to US in 2026]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131210895.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/indian-man-says-us-is-no-longer-a-default-upgrade-3-types-of-people-should-not-come-to-us-in-2026/articleshow/131210895.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/indian-man-says-us-is-no-longer-a-default-upgrade-3-types-of-people-should-not-come-to-us-in-2026/articleshow/131210895.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T01:52:56+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131210921,imgsize-112188.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Logan Paul reacts in disbelief as streamer Clavicular admits extreme body enhancement habits linked to controversial looksmaxxing culture online]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131210860.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Logan Paul was left stunned after influencer Clavicular described extreme body enhancement methods during an Impaulsive podcast episode. The interview quickly went viral because of the influencer’s unusual admissions and controversial opinions. Medical experts featured on 60 Minutes have already warned people that dangerous looksmaxxing practices can lead to serious physical risks and harmful emotional effects over time.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/logan-paul-reacts-in-disbelief-as-streamer-clavicular-admits-extreme-body-enhancement-habits-linked-to-controversial-looksmaxxing-culture-online/articleshow/131210860.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/logan-paul-reacts-in-disbelief-as-streamer-clavicular-admits-extreme-body-enhancement-habits-linked-to-controversial-looksmaxxing-culture-online/articleshow/131210860.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-20T01:32:15+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131210856,imgsize-32870.cms"/></item></channel></rss>